n discourse and global events allows Grok to achieve industry-leading performance in freshness, relevance, and contextual awareness.\n* **User Metrics:** As of March 31, 2026, the integrated platforms had over 1.3 billion supported accounts, including **550 million Monthly Active Users (MAUs)**. Of those, approximately **117 million MAUs** actively used Grok’s AI features.\n* **Monetization:** X monetizes this ecosystem through X Premium subscriptions (Basic, Premium, Premium+) which offer priority Grok interactions, as well as through high-impact advertising and enterprise deployments (Grok Business and Grok Enterprise).\n\n#### B. Gigawatt-Scale AI Compute Infrastructure\n* **COLOSSUS Clusters:** xAI has established a massive terrestrial AI compute infrastructure. COLOSSUS and COLOSSUS II collectively provide approximately **1.0 gigawatt** of compute power. \n* **Speed and Efficiency:** The first COLOSSUS cluster was brought online in just 122 days. COLOSSUS II utilizes a behind-the-meter natural gas power plant and the world’s largest Megapack deployment to ensure cost-efficient, reliable power for training next-generation models like Grok 5.\n* **Orbital Data Centers:** Following SpaceX\'s acquisition of xAI, the company envisions leveraging SpaceX\'s reusable rockets to deploy massive AI compute satellite constellations in Sun-synchronous orbit to handle energy-intensive AI workloads.\n\n#### C. Strategic Partnerships & Compute Monetization\nTo offset infrastructure costs and vertically integrate into high-value workflows, the company is monetizing excess compute and partnering with key software players:\n* **Anthropic:** In May 2026, the company entered into a Cloud Services Agreement with Anthropic, yielding **$1.25 billion per month** through May 2029 for access to COLOSSUS compute capacity.\n* **Cursor (Anysphere):** The company entered into a compute and option agreement with the AI coding tool Cursor. This provides Cursor with GPU capacity while giving xA