        output='Based on the provided S-1 prospectus excerpts, here are the details regarding the March 2025 merger where xAI acquired X Holdings, as well as the associated terms, payments, and pre-merger agreements. \n\n*Note: The text distinguishes between the **"X Merger"** (xAI acquiring X Holdings in March 2025) and the subsequent **"xAI Merger"** (SpaceX acquiring xAI in February 2026). The answers below focus primarily on the X Merger and the ecosystem of agreements involving these entities.*\n\n### 1. Terms of the Merger (xAI acquiring X Holdings)\n* **Effective Date:** March 28, 2025.\n* **Structure:** The transaction was effected through a **share exchange**, resulting in X Holdings Corp. (“X”) and X.AI Corp. becoming wholly-owned subsidiaries of xAI.\n* **Accounting Treatment:** Because Elon Musk held a controlling financial/majority voting interest in all entities involved, the merger was accounted for as a **reorganization of entities under common control**. \n* **Financial Recasting:** The net assets of the entities were combined retrospectively at their historical carrying amounts. No new goodwill or intangible assets were recorded, and all historical intercompany/related-party transactions between the entities were eliminated in consolidation.\n\n### 2. What xAI Paid for X\nxAI paid for the acquisition entirely in **equity (stock)** via the share exchange; no cash consideration is mentioned for this specific leg of the transaction.\n* **Common Stock Exchange Ratio:** Each class of X Holdings Corp. common stock was converted into **2.776 shares** of xAI Common Stock of the corresponding class (rounded down to the nearest whole share).\n* **RSU Conversion:** Each outstanding X Restricted Stock Unit (RSU) was converted into an xAI RSU representing the right to receive **2.776 shares** of xAI stock, maintaining the exact same terms, conditions, and vesting schedules as the original X awards.\n\n### 3. Services Exchanged Before the Merger\nThe provided text explicitly states that *"all historical related party transactions between the entities [SpaceX, xAI, and X] have been eliminated in consolidation."* Therefore, **the specific internal services exchanged directly between xAI and X prior to the merger are not detailed in this excerpt.**\n\nHowever, the text *does* detail the services and transactions that xAI and X exchanged with **other affiliated entities** (such as Tesla, The Boring Company, and Valor Equity Partners) prior to and during the merger periods:\n* **xAI & Tesla:** xAI obtained goods and services from Tesla (e.g., $191M in 2024; $506M in 2025) and recognized revenue from Tesla for AI-related services ($2M in 2025).\n* **X Holdings & Tesla:** Tesla purchased advertising on the X platform ($0.5M in 2024; $4M in 2025).\n* **X & The Boring Company:** X leased office space from a subsidiary of The Boring Company starting in 2024.\n* **xAI & Valor Equity Partners:** xAI subsidiaries leased massive amounts of computing equipment from Valor. In return, X provided API services to Valor ($1M in 2024; $1M in 2025).\n\n### 4. Pre-Merger Agreements (and Ongoing Related-Party Contracts)\nThe prospectus lists several major agreements entered into by xAI or X prior to the SpaceX/xAI merger that remained ongoing or impacted the consolidated entity:\n\n**Debt and Financing Agreements:**\n* **First Lien Credit Agreement (June 2025):** xAI subsidiaries entered into a **$2 Billion** credit facility consisting of a $1B Fixed Rate Term Loan (12.50% interest) and a $1B Floating Rate Term Loan (SOFR + 7.25%), both maturing in 2030. These borrowings are **guaranteed by SpaceX**.\n* **Computing Equipment Leases (Valor Equity Partners):** xAI subsidiaries entered into three massive equipment lease agreements with Valor for computing infrastructure. The aggregate cash payments over the life of these leases total **$20.2 Billion** ($6,986M + $6,633M + $6,587M). These lease obligations are also **guaranteed by SpaceX**.\n\n**Investment Agreements:**\n* **Tesla’s Investment in xAI (January 2026):** Tesla entered into an agreement to invest **$2 Billion** in xAI via the purchase of Series E Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock. (Following the SpaceX merger, this right was converted into SpaceX Class A Common Stock, and 3.8 million pre-split shares were issued to Tesla in March 2026).\n\n**Employment and Compensation Agreements:**\n* **Elon Musk’s Performance Stock Award (November 2025):** xAI granted a performance stock award to Elon Musk tied to 12 valuation milestones (ranging from $1.065T to $6.565T). SpaceX assumed this award during the 2026 merger, adjusting it to reflect SpaceX Class A common stock (0.20% of fully diluted capitalization per milestone). The first milestone was achieved pre-merger, resulting in an initial issuance of ~25.1 million shares.',
